
##  XSS Vulnerability Report
1. Vulnerability Details

* Vulnerability Type: Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)
* Severity: Medium to High (depending on impact, e.g., session hijacking)
* Affected Endpoint: https://insecure-website.com/search?term=gift

2. Vulnerability Description
The application fails to properly sanitize or encode user-supplied input. When the user input is reflected in the server’s HTTP response, it is executed as code by the victim's browser. This exposes users to risks like cookie theft and unauthorized actions. [7, 11, 12] 
3. Steps to Reproduce (Proof of Concept)

   1. Navigate to the vulnerable input field (e.g., Search Bar or User Profile).
   2. Inject the following benign payload into the field:
   <script>alert('XSS_Vulnerability_Confirmed')</script>
   3. Submit the form.
   4. Result: An alert popup appears, demonstrating that arbitrary JavaScript has successfully executed in the browser context. [3, 13, 14, 15, 16] 

4. Impact
An attacker could leverage this vulnerability to steal session cookies, log keystrokes, or perform unauthorized actions on behalf of the authenticated user. [7, 17] 
5. Remediation

* Output Encoding: Encode all user-supplied data before rendering it in the HTML context (e.g., converting < to &lt;).
* Input Validation: Employ strict whitelisting to filter out disallowed characters.
* Security Headers: Implement a strong Content Security Policy (CSP) to restrict where scripts can load from and execute. [18, 19, 20, 21, 22] 

